Hereâ€™s a simple README file for a GitHub repository that includes instructions on checking the Docker version:  

---

// Docker Version Check  
 docker -v

// Download an image from docker hub
docker pull hello-world

// To check the docker images in local host machine
docker images

//To run a container from docker images
 docker run hello-world

// To check running container
 docker ps

//To check all container (running and stop)
 docker ps -a


*** suppose I need to install an ubuntu container***

docker run -it ubuntu
// here -it --> interactive modes

//to check the container
docker ps

// to stop running container
docker stop container_id/name

// to start a container
docker start container_id/name


// to delete a container from local host machine
docker rm container_id/name

// to delete a docker images from local host machine 
docker rmi container_id/name

// pull an image from docker hub and run a container from this image
docker pull image_name

// to run a container for specific time
docker run image_name sleep 200
// here 200 means 200 seconds.

// Docker environment
 docker run -d -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=jahid mysql
 ..... MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=jahid is an environment for creating a password
 ..... -d means  detached mode, allows containers to run in the background, freeing up your terminal for other tasks, without requiring direct input or output



